 This function calculates the nth element of the FibFib sequence efficiently using dynamic programming. The time complexity of this solution is O(N).

```php
<?php

/**
 * Calculate the n-th element of the FibFib sequence efficiently.
 * @param int $n The index of the element to calculate.
 * @return int The value of the n-th element in the FibFib sequence.
 */
function fibfib($n) {
    // Initialize an array to store the sequence values.
    $sequence = [0, 0, 1];

    // Calculate and add subsequent elements to the sequence using dynamic programming.
    for ($i = 3; $i <= $n; $i++) {
        $sequence[] = $sequence[$i - 1] + $sequence[$i - 2] + $sequence[$i - 3];
    }

    // Return the n-th element of the sequence.
    return $sequence[$n];
}
```

This function uses dynamic programming to efficiently calculate the n-th element of the FibFib sequence. It initializes an array with the first three elements of the sequence (0, 0, and 1) and then iteratively calculates subsequent elements by adding the previous three elements together. Finally, it returns the n-th element of the sequence.

Note that this function assumes that the input $n is a non-negative integer. If you need to handle negative values or floating-point numbers, you'll need to add additional logic to handle those cases.

